objecttypes.name: EntityType
objecttypes.description: An EntityType represents a category or class of similar entities in a data model, For example, a 'Customer' could be an EntityType with relationships to properties like name and address.

objecttypes.name: Information
objecttypes.description: Defines an Information element with Name, description and proposedType properties.

objecttypes.name: Role
objecttypes.description: A process role defines the responsibilities and authority of individuals involved in a business process. These roles help clarify who is accountable for various tasks, ensuring efficient process management and execution.

objecttypes.name: Task
objecttypes.description: A task is a specific, defined activity or piece of work that contributes to the completion of a larger project or process.

objecttypes.name: View
objecttypes.description: A View highlight essential Information elements tailored to the need of specific users or tasks.

objecttypes.name: Property
objecttypes.description: A property is an object representing an attribute of an entity that holds basic data, such as strings, numbers, or booleans. It defines specific characteristics of the entity, like 'name' or 'age'.
